<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="045" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>AssignWorkWizardLauncher — Xrm.Navigation dispatcher for sprk_createworkassignmentwizard (FR-20)</title>
    <phase>Phase D — Context pane</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks></blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, dataverse, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Crosses the host boundary into Dataverse via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo — a host-only API. Feature-detection + Vite-dev placeholder is required (per A-2 + FR-20). UQ-05 unresolved: exact `data` query string format must be verified from user-provided runtime log before going live. Touches the GetStartedCards wiring path (task 042) and must align with its dispatch contract. Risk R-7 explicit in plan §8.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `AssignWorkWizardLauncher` — a thin dispatcher that invokes the existing Dataverse
    custom page `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard` via `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` per FR-20.
    Feature-detect `window.Xrm`: in the Power Apps host, call the navigation API; in
    non-host environments (Vite dev), render a placeholder banner with "Open in Spaarke
    (host required)" copy. Coordinate with task 042's onCardClick dispatcher so the
    Assign Work card invokes this launcher (mechanism flexible — either direct function call
    or a special widget_type the launcher subscribes to). UQ-05 mandates verifying the
    exact `data` query string format against the user-provided runtime log before going live.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent v9 frontend developer experienced with Dataverse host-API integration
    (Xrm.Navigation), feature detection for cross-environment compatibility, and thin
    dispatcher patterns. Familiar with the spaarke `bffBaseUrl` query parameter contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts`
    exists and exports a `launchAssignWorkWizard(opts: { bffBaseUrl: string })` function (or
    a small React component if the wiring chosen with task 042 is component-based). The
    function:
    (a) Feature-detects `window.Xrm`. If absent, returns / renders a placeholder result
        indicating non-host environment.
    (b) If `window.Xrm` is present, calls `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({ pageType: 'custom',
        name: 'sprk_createworkassignmentwizard', data: 'bffBaseUrl=' + encodeURIComponent(bffBaseUrl) })`
        — with the EXACT `data` format verified against the user-provided runtime log
        (UQ-05).
    Task 042's onCardClick handler is updated (or coordinated) to invoke this launcher when
    the Assign Work card is clicked.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-20 routes the Assign Work GetStartedCards card to an EXISTING Dataverse custom page,
      `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard`. Unlike the other 6 cards (which route to in-app
      widgets in the Workspace pane), Assign Work crosses the host boundary via
      `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` — opening a Dataverse-hosted dialog rather than a tab in
      the Workspace pane. This requires feature-detection because Vite dev does not have
      `window.Xrm`. UQ-05 is unresolved: the user provided a runtime log showing the exact
      query string format that `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard` expects. Verify the
      format against that log before shipping (failure mode: silent dialog dismissal or
      missing parameters).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">If a placeholder UI is needed for non-host environments, keep it inline / minimal — do NOT introduce a new shared component for one placeholder banner. Use the simplest Fluent v9 banner / MessageBar inline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Placeholder banner styling uses Fluent v9 tokens only. No hex literals.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19. No React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">`bffBaseUrl` is the Spaarke BFF base URL — sourced from environment / configuration, NOT a token. Do NOT pass any access token through the `data` query string (that would violate ADR-028). The Dataverse-hosted custom page is responsible for its own auth flow.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">A-2: `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo` is unavailable in Vite dev — feature-detect `window.Xrm` and show "Open in Spaarke" placeholder. UQ-05: exact `data` query string format MUST be verified from user-provided runtime log before going live. R-7 risk register entry tracks this.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Coordinate with task 042: the Assign Work card click must invoke this launcher. Either (a) task 042's onCardClick special-cases the `assign-work` widget_type and calls `launchAssignWorkWizard()` directly, OR (b) registers a subscriber on a dedicated event type. Choose the simplest option that keeps task 042's onCardClick handler readable.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/dialog-patterns.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Verify the data query string format (UQ-05)">
      Locate the user-provided runtime log for `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard`. Confirm the
      exact `data` parameter format. Verify URL-encoding semantics (`encodeURIComponent` vs.
      `encodeURI` vs. raw). Document the verified format in the launcher file header. If the
      log is unavailable, escalate via 🔔 Human Input Required before proceeding.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Determine bffBaseUrl source">
      Identify where `bffBaseUrl` is configured in SpaarkeAi (likely via environment variable
      or a config module). Document the source so the launcher can either accept it as a prop
      (deferring sourcing to the caller) OR read it directly (simpler API for task 042).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Scaffold AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts">
      Create the file. Export `launchAssignWorkWizard(opts: { bffBaseUrl: string })`:
      <steps>
        <step>Feature-detect `typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.Xrm?.Navigation?.navigateTo`.</step>
        <step>If absent, return / show placeholder (see step 4).</step>
        <step>If present, call `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({ pageType: 'custom', name: 'sprk_createworkassignmentwizard', data: 'bffBaseUrl=' + encodeURIComponent(bffBaseUrl) })` with the exact format verified in step 1.</step>
      </steps>
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement non-host placeholder">
      If the wiring with task 042 is function-based (most likely), the placeholder is just a
      `console.warn` / toast / temporary banner indicating "Open in Spaarke (host required)".
      If the wiring is a widget-component-based subscriber (less likely), render a small
      Fluent v9 MessageBar in the Workspace pane explaining the host requirement.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Coordinate with task 042 onCardClick wiring">
      Update task 042's onCardClick handler (or coordinate via a comment in the launcher
      file) so that the Assign Work card click invokes `launchAssignWorkWizard()` instead of
      dispatching a `widget_load` event on the `workspace` channel. The simplest mechanism
      is special-casing the `assign-work` widget_type in task 042's handler.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Smoke-test in both environments">
      Build SpaarkeAi. In Power Apps host: click Assign Work card → confirm
      `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard` opens (verify the dialog reads the bffBaseUrl correctly
      and proceeds with its own flow). In Vite dev: click Assign Work → confirm placeholder
      message appears (toast / banner / log) and no console error fires.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read user-provided runtime log + bffBaseUrl config source</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Possibly coordinate update with task 042 (special-case assign-work in its onCardClick)</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find bffBaseUrl config source + existing Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo usage as reference</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run `npm run build` against Spaarke.AI.Widgets</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report confirming launcher feature-detects, verified data format, and Assign Work click works in both Power Apps host and Vite dev</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`AssignWorkWizardLauncher.ts` exists and exports `launchAssignWorkWizard()` (or canonical name).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Function feature-detects `window.Xrm` before calling `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">In the Power Apps host, clicking Assign Work invokes `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo({ pageType: 'custom', name: 'sprk_createworkassignmentwizard', data: '...' })` with the EXACT `data` format verified against the user-provided runtime log (UQ-05).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">In Vite dev, clicking Assign Work shows a non-host placeholder (banner / toast / warning) without throwing.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Task 042's onCardClick handler invokes this launcher for the Assign Work card (coordinated wiring).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No access tokens passed through the `data` query string (ADR-028 invariant preserved).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No hex literals, no `rgba(...)` literals in placeholder UI.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`npm run build` succeeds with no new TS / lint errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Assign Work in Power Apps host opens custom page">
      Deploy SpaarkeAi to the Dataverse test environment. Load the welcome state in the Power Apps
      host. Click the Assign Work card. Confirm the Dataverse custom page
      `sprk_createworkassignmentwizard` opens as a dialog (not in the Workspace pane). Verify the
      page reads the bffBaseUrl parameter and proceeds normally.
    </test>
    <test name="Assign Work in Vite dev shows placeholder">
      In Vite dev (`npm run dev` against SpaarkeAi), load the welcome state. Click the Assign Work
      card. Confirm a placeholder banner / toast / warning appears with "Open in Spaarke (host required)"
      copy (or equivalent). No console error fires; no exception thrown.
    </test>
    <test name="Other GetStartedCards still work">
      With Assign Work special-cased in task 042's onCardClick, verify the other 6 cards still open
      their respective widgets (regression check for the dispatcher's switch / mapping logic).
    </test>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021, NFR-06)">
      If a placeholder banner is shown in dark mode, confirm it adapts via Fluent v9 tokens (no hex
      leaks, no white in dark mode).
    </test>
    <test name="No console errors in either environment">
      Open browser devtools in both Power Apps host and Vite dev. Click Assign Work in each. Confirm
      zero JavaScript errors or React warnings.
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

